  "prompt": "How can I apply for internship at Google? Is there age limit?",
  "response": "To apply for an internship at Google, follow these steps:\n\n1. Eligibility Requirements:\n- Currently enrolled in a bachelor's, master's, or PhD program\n- Strong academic performance\n- Demonstrated technical skills\n- No strict upper age limit, but typically for current students\n\n2. Application Process:\n- Visit careers.google.com\n- Select \"Students\" or \"Internships\"\n- Browse available internship positions\n- Create a profile\n- Upload your resume\n- Submit online application\n\n3. Types of Internships:\n- Software Engineering\n- Business/Marketing\n- Design\n- Research\n- Product Management\n\n4. Key Tips:\n- Apply early (often 8-12 months in advance)\n- Highlight relevant skills and projects\n- Prepare for technical interviews\n- Strong programming/coding skills preferred\n- Internships are often for current students\n\n5. Locations:\n- Internships available globally\n- Major concentrations in US (Mountain View, CA)\n\n6. General Requirements:\n- Good GPA (typically 3.0+)\n- Programming knowledge\n- Problem-solving skills\n- Communication abilities\n\nRecommendation: Check Google's official careers website for most current details and specific position requirements.",
